Quote:  The N. and N.E. winds, which draw up the harbour [at Port Ashley : ?Lyttelton], are seldom either violent or enduring; from the appearance of the hills, I supposed it subject to flurries in N.W. and S.W. gales; ... the former wind draws up Port Cooper, ... and the latter draws down ...
Notes:  1842 Capt. Smith's report (p292) in 1848 Wakefield Handbook for NZ 328
